- Listen, if Western companies have already decided to leave Russia, then why do not all of them leave at once, but one at a time? - You see, their goal is not to harden, but to wear them out. A bucket of ice water is hardening. But a drop of cold water on the temechko around the clock is torture. Therefore, they leave strictly according to the “launched from above” schedule, but no one forces you to stand under a drop!